er automating workflows, a team lead building custom AI tools, or a hobbyist exploring AI coding assistants, you'll find skills for every use case. All skills use the open SKILL.md standard, compatible with Claude Code, OpenAI Codex CLI, and other tools adopting this format.\n              - generic [ref=e1003]: \"[INFO] Ready to explore the largest collection of agent skills for AI coding assistants?\"\n          - generic [ref=e1004]:\n            - generic [ref=e1005]:\n              - button \"Browse\" [ref=e1006]:\n                - generic [ref=e1007]:\n                  - img [ref=e1008]\n                  - generic [ref=e1011]: Browse\n              - button \"Easy\" [ref=e1012]:\n                - generic [ref=e1013]:\n                  - img [ref=e1014]\n                  - generic [ref=e1016]: Easy\n              - button \"GitHub\" [ref=e1017]:\n                - generic [ref=e1018]:\n                  - img [ref=e1019]\n                  - generic [ref=e1022]: GitHub\n            - generic [ref=e1023]:\n              - generic [ref=e1024]:\n                - text: export const Browse&Discover\n                - generic [ref=e1025]: \"= () => {\"\n              - generic [ref=e1027]:\n                - generic [ref=e1028]: return\n                - img [ref=e1030]\n              - generic [ref=e1033]:\n                - generic [ref=e1034]: /**\n                - generic [ref=e1035]: \"* Search through 200000++ agent skills with intelligent filtering by category, author, and popularity. Compatible with Claude Code, Codex CLI and ChatGPT.\"\n                - generic [ref=e1036]: \"*/\"\n              - generic [ref=e1037]: \"}\"\n        - region \"# Frequently Asked Questions\" [ref=e1042]:\n          - generic [ref=e1044]:\n            - generic [ref=e1045]:\n              - generic [ref=e1051]: FAQ.md\n              - generic [ref=e1052]: 8 questions\n            - generic [ref=e1053]:\n              - heading \"# Frequently Asked Questions\" [level=2] [ref=e1054]\n              - paragraph [ref=e1055]: Everything you need to know about agent skills, Claude Code, OpenAI Codex, and AI coding tools in 2025\n          - generic [ref=e1056]:\n            - article [ref=e1058]:\n              - 'button \"01 Q: What are Agent Skills? [+]\" [ref=e1059] [cursor=pointer]':\n                - generic [ref=e1060]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1061]: \"01\"\n                  - 'heading \"Q: What are Agent Skills?\" [level=3] [ref=e1062]'\n                - generic [ref=e1063]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1064]: \"[+]\"\n                  - img [ref=e1065]\n              - generic [ref=e1068]:\n                - generic [ref=e1069]: /**\n                - generic [ref=e1070]: \"* Agent Skills are modular capabilities that extend AI coding assistants. Each skill consists of a SKILL.md file with instructions, plus optional scripts and templates. In December 2025, Anthropic released the Agent Skills specification as an open standard, and OpenAI adopted the same format for Codex CLI and ChatGPT. Skills are model-invoked—the AI automatically decides when to use them based on context.\"\n                - generic [ref=e1071]: \"*/\"\n            - article [ref=e1073]:\n              - 'button \"02 Q: How do I install an agent skill? [+]\" [ref=e1074] [cursor=pointer]':\n                - generic [ref=e1075]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1076]: \"02\"\n                  - 'heading \"Q: How do I install an agent skill?\" [level=3] [ref=e1077]'\n                - generic [ref=e1078]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1079]: \"[+]\"\n                  - img [ref=e1080]\n              - generic [ref=e1083]:\n                - generic [ref=e1084]: /**\n                - generic [ref=e1085]: \"* For Claude Code: Add to ~/.claude/skills/ (personal) or .claude/skills/ (project). For OpenAI Codex CLI: Add to ~/.codex/skills/. Both use the same SKILL.md format. Clone the GitHub repository and copy the skill folder to your chosen directory. The AI automatically discovers and loads skills from these locations.\"\n                - generic [ref=e1086]: \"*/\"\n            - article [ref=e1088]:\n              - 'button \"03 Q: Are these skills safe to use? [+]\" [ref=e1089] [cursor=pointer]':\n                - generic [ref=e1090]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1091]: \"03\"\n                  - 'heading \"Q: Are these skills safe to use?\" [level=3] [ref=e1092]'\n                - generic [ref=e1093]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1094]: \"[+]\"\n                  - img [ref=e1095]\n              - generic [ref=e1098]:\n                - generic [ref=e1099]: /**\n                - generic [ref=e1100]: \"* Skills from this marketplace are sourced from public GitHub repositories. We filter out low-quality repos (minimum 2 stars) and scan for basic quality indicators, but you should always review the code before installing. Community skills should be treated like any open-source code—inspect before use.\"\n                - generic [ref=e1101]: \"*/\"\n            - article [ref=e1103]:\n              - 'button \"04 Q: Can I use multiple skills together? [+]\" [ref=e1104] [cursor=pointer]':\n                - generic [ref=e1105]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1106]: \"04\"\n                  - 'heading \"Q: Can I use multiple skills together?\" [level=3] [ref=e1107]'\n                - generic [ref=e1108]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1109]: \"[+]\"\n                  - img [ref=e1110]\n              - generic [ref=e1113]:\n                - generic [ref=e1114]: /**\n                - generic [ref=e1115]: \"* Yes! Claude Code supports multiple skills simultaneously. Skills are modular and designed to work together. For example, you can combine a 'code-reviewer' skill with a 'git-automation' skill to automatically review and commit code changes. Claude intelligently selects the appropriate skills based on your request context.\"\n                - generic [ref=e1116]: \"*/\"\n            - article [ref=e1118]:\n              - 'button \"05 Q: Can I create and share my own skills? [+]\" [ref=e1119] [cursor=pointer]':\n                - generic [ref=e1120]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1121]: \"05\"\n                  - 'heading \"Q: Can I create and share my own skills?\" [level=3] [ref=e1122]'\n                - generic [ref=e1123]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1124]: \"[+]\"\n                  - img [ref=e1125]\n              - generic [ref=e1128]:\n                - generic [ref=e1129]: /**\n                - generic [ref=e1130]: \"* Yes! You can create custom Claude skills and share them on GitHub. Check out the skill-creator skill for detailed guidance on creating your own skills. The basic structure requires a SKILL.md file with instructions. You can also add optional scripts and templates.\"\n                - generic [ref=e1131]: \"*/\"\n            - article [ref=e1133]:\n              - 'button \"06 Q: How do skills differ from slash commands? [+]\" [ref=e1134] [cursor=pointer]':\n                - generic [ref=e1135]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1136]: \"06\"\n                  - 'heading \"Q: How do skills differ from slash commands?\" [level=3] [ref=e1137]'\n                - generic [ref=e1138]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1139]: \"[+]\"\n                  - img [ref=e1140]\n              - generic [ref=e1143]:\n                - generic [ref=e1144]: /**\n                - generic [ref=e1145]: \"* Skills are model-invoked—Claude automatically decides when to use them based on context. Slash commands are user-invoked—you explicitly type the command to trigger them. Skills enable more intelligent, context-aware automation in your workflows.\"\n                - generic [ref=e1146]: \"*/\"\n            - article [ref=e1148]:\n              - 'button \"07 Q: How often are skills updated? [+]\" [ref=e1149] [cursor=pointer]':\n                - generic [ref=e1150]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1151]: \"07\"\n                  - 'heading \"Q: How often are skills updated?\" [level=3] [ref=e1152]'\n                - generic [ref=e1153]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1154]: \"[+]\"\n                  - img [ref=e1155]\n              - generic [ref=e1158]:\n                - generic [ref=e1159]: /**\n                - generic [ref=e1160]: \"* Our scraper regularly syncs with GitHub to fetch the latest skills and updates. When a skill repository is updated on GitHub, the changes will appear on SkillsMP shortly after our next sync. You can see the last update timestamp on each skill card. We recommend checking back regularly for new skills and improvements to existing ones.\"\n                - generic [ref=e1161]: \"*/\"\n            - article [ref=e1163]:\n              - 'button \"08 Q: Is this website affiliated with Anthropic or OpenAI? [+]\" [ref=e1164] [cursor=pointer]':\n                - generic [ref=e1165]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1166]: \"08\"\n                  - 'heading \"Q: Is this website affiliated with Anthropic or OpenAI?\" [level=3] [ref=e1167]'\n                - generic [ref=e1168]:\n                  - generic [ref=e1169]: \"[+]\"\n                  - img [ref=e1170]\n              - generic [ref=e1173]:\n                - generic [ref=e1174]: /**\n                - generic [ref=e1175]: \"* No, SkillsMP is an independent community project. We aggregate and showcase agent skills from GitHub to make discovery easier. For official skills and documentation, refer to Anthropic's github.com/anthropics/skills or OpenAI's Codex documentation.\"\n                - generic [ref=e1176]: \"*/\"\n          - generic [ref=e1177]:\n            - paragraph [ref=e1178]: Still have questions about agent skills?\n            - link \"$ open /docs && explore\" [ref=e1179] [cursor=pointer]:\n              - /url: /en/docs\n              - generic [ref=e1180]: $\n              - generic [ref=e1181]: open\n              - generic [ref=e1182]: /docs\n              - generic [ref=e1183]: \"&&\"\n              - generic [ref=e1184]: explore\n              - img [ref=e1185]\n    - contentinfo [ref=e1187]:\n      - generic [ref=e1189]:\n        - generic [ref=e1190]:\n          - generic [ref=e1191]:\n            - generic [ref=e1192]: $ cat README.md\n            - heading \"# Skills Marketplace\" [level=2] [ref=e1193]\n          - paragraph [ref=e1194]: Discover and explore AI skills built by the community.\n        - generic [ref=e1195]:\n          - generic [ref=e1196]:\n            - generic [ref=e1197]: $ git remote -v\n            - list [ref=e1198]:\n              - listitem [ref=e1199]:\n                - link \"Twitter\" [ref=e1200] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - /url: https://x.com/God_I_13\n                  - img [ref=e1201]\n                  - text: Twitter\n              - listitem [ref=e1203]:\n                - link \"GitHub\" [ref=e1204] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - /url: https://github.com/Godi13\n                  - img [ref=e1205]\n                  - text: GitHub\n              - listitem [ref=e1208]:\n                - link \"Reddit\" [ref=e1209] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - /url: https://www.reddit.com/user/TingXuSuan/\n                  - img [ref=e1210]\n                  - text: Reddit\n          - generic [ref=e1212]:\n            - generic [ref=e1213]: $ ls ./resources/\n            - list [ref=e1214]:\n              - listitem [ref=e1215]:\n                - link \"📚 Skills Docs\" [ref=e1216] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - /url: /en/docs\n                  - generic [ref=e1217]: 📚\n                  - text: Skills Docs\n              - listitem [ref=e1218]:\n                - link \"📄 Skill Document\" [ref=e1219] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - /url: https://code.claude.com/docs/en/skills\n                  - generic [ref=e1220]: 📄\n                  - text: Skill Document\n              - listitem [ref=e1221]:\n                - lin