{"type":"message","id":"3c9c9edf","parentId":"42a6e059","timestamp":"2026-02-15T09:39:52.442Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### Skills & Capabilities Audit (Phase 2) - Final Report\n\n#### 1. SkillsMP Verification (https://skillsmp.com/)\n*   **Is SkillsMP real?** **YES**. It is a functional AI agent marketplace (v0.1.0) specializing in the `SKILL.md` ecosystem, compatible with Claude Code and OpenClaw.\n*   **Findings**:\n    *   **Browsed Categories**: Checked `/categories/development` and `/categories/databases`.\n    *   **Specific Skills**: Found several high-utility skills including `aoti-debug` (97k downloads), `coding-agent` (192k downloads), and `gog` (Google Workspace CLI).\n    *   **API Key Requirements**: The FAQ states that skills are model-invoked and usually local scripts, but specific skills (like `tavily-search`) require their own external API keys. There is no central SkillsMP API key required for browsing or downloading.\n\n#### 2. ClawHub Verification (https://clawhub.ai)\n*   **Status**: Active \"skill dock\" for OpenClaw. Note: The URL is `clawhub.ai` (redirects from `.com`).\n*   **Search Results for Requested Skills**:\n    *   `context-optimizer` / `memory-manager`: No direct matches found by name, but found **`self-improving-agent`** (21k downloads) which captures learnings/corrections and **`Ontology`** (14k downloads) for structured agent memory.\n    *   `pwsh-helper` / `shell-improver`: No specific PowerShell-optimized helper found, though general coding agents like `coding-agent` are available.\n    *   `secret-manager`: No direct hit for a PowerShell SecretManagement GUI/helper.\n    *   `self-diagnosis` / `doctor-pro`: Found **`auto-updater`** for system maintenance and **`self-improving-agent`** for error correction.\n\n#### 3. Comparative Analysis & Top Recommendations\nSkillsMP serves as a large aggregator (214k+ skills) primarily indexing GitHub repositories, while ClawHub acts as a curated \"dock\" with versioning and high-signal picks.\n\n**TOP 3 Recommended Skills for an \"Architect\" Agent:**\n\n1.  **`self-improving-agent`** (ClawHub: `@pskoett/self-improving-agent`)\n    *   **Why**: Crucial for an Architect. It captures errors, corrections, and new patterns, allowing the agent to \"learn\" from its mistakes and user feedback over time.\n    *   **Install**: `openclaw skills add pskoett/self-improving-agent`\n\n2.  **`coding-agent`** (SkillsMP: `openclaw/openclaw/skills/coding-agent.md`)\n    *   **Why**: Provides programmatic control over other coding agents (Claude Code, Codex). Essential for orchestrating complex multi-agent workflows.\n    *   **Install**: `openclaw skills add openclaw/coding-agent`\n\n3.  **`Ontology`** (ClawHub: `@oswalpalash/ontology`)\n    *   **Why**: Provides a typed knowledge graph for structured memory. Instead of raw text logs, it allows the Architect to store relationships between projects, tasks, and entities.\n    *   **Install**: `openclaw skills add oswalpalash/ontology`\n\n#### 4. Summary Table\n| Feature | SkillsMP (skillsmp.com) | ClawHub (clawhub.ai) |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Real?** | Yes | Yes |\n| **Focus** | GitHub Aggregator (SKILL.md) | Curated Signal & Versioning |\n| **API Keys** | Per-skill only | Per-skill only |\n| **Best For** | Discovering niche tools | Reliable, battle-tested skills |\n| **Top Pick** | `coding-agent` | `self-improving-agent` |","textSignature":"CiEBjz1rXy5nipE/1zbv07fpHlQ+oJCrUNqG6apwwQPfi1E="}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":49999,"output":883,"cacheRead":37485,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50882,"cost":{"input":0.024999499999999997,"output":0.002649,"cacheRead":0.0018742500000000003,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.029522749999999997}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771148385298}}
